iance of positivism and plutocracy. It offers a nonideological ethical alternative, a way out and up, in the nobility of one human being helping another, and the solidarity that moves from morality to justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aJewish philosophy. 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Philosophy. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846111340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438461113423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438461113/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles